The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Ritu to officiate 
Mumbai: Former player Ritu Sharma is to officiate at the most prestigious Grand Slam event on the tennis calendar  the All England Championships in Wimbledon, her father and tennis official M.K. Sethi told reporters here on Thursday night. Sethi, who is the All India Tennis Association (AITA) supervisor for the May 24-29 Matunga Gymkhana all-India ranking juniors tennis tournament, said that Ritu would also be officiating at the US Open in August. Ritu, a qualified ITF Level II official, will be the first woman from India to officiate in three Grand Slam tournaments, having earlier done the job at the Australian Open in January. This is for the second successive year that Ritu will be officiating at Wimbledon, Sethi said. Meanwhile, senior chair umpire Nitin Kannamwar has been chosen to officiate at the French Open, beginning May 24, by the ITF. Kannamwar will also officiate at Wimbledon along with Payal Jain, the youngest brown badge woman umpire in Asia, and Ritu, Maharashtra State Lawn Tennis Association (Mslta) secretary Sharad Kannamwar said on Friday. (PTI)  Copyright 
